Constructor Detail

WikiCorrelator

public WikiCorrelator(java.lang.String source,
                      java.lang.String destination,
                      int maxHops,
                      int msgLevel,
                      int timeout)
Constructor for WikiCorrelator class. Note that source and destination articles will take additional hops if not in correct format and have to be special-searched due to case, spacing, etc.

Parameters:
source - The title of article to begin
destination - The destination target article title
maxHops - Maximum # of hops (levels) to traverse
msgLevel - Display console output up to this many hops
timeout - How long to wait for the HTTP request response
Method Detail

hasPathTo

private boolean hasPathTo(java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> path,
                          java.lang.String url,
                          int hops)
Recursive depth-first graph search to determine a Wikipedia article node has a possible path to the class target destination URL. Called by find()

Parameters:
path - Current path state
url - The URL to be parsed
hops - The current # of hops taken to arrive at this point
Returns:
True if a path exists to the given URL

getNumResults

public int getNumResults()
Get the number of results

Returns:
Number of results found. Zero if WikiCorrelator has not been started using find()

find

public java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> find()
Execute the WikiCorrelator search. Uses hasPathTo(Vector, String, int) greedy DFS to find a correlation between two Wikipedia articles.

Returns:
A Vector list of the path taken. Will return an empty list if no valid path is found.

formatSearchString

public java.lang.String formatSearchString(java.lang.String query)
Utility function to format the URL title to a more Wikipedia-like style.

Parameters:
query - Search query of article title
Returns:
String with the /wiki/ prefix and spaces replaced by underscores.

Main console entry point
